        <div class="card">
          <h2>Fuji film simulation recipes</h2>
          <p>Classic Chrome, Portra-inspired looks, moody night recipes—settings shared in a consistent format.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Lightroom preset settings</h2>
          <p>Not just “buy my preset”—actual sliders and values so you can learn and iterate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>LUT recipes for video</h2>
          <p>Colorists can share LUTs with before/after samples and the context behind the grade.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Film stock recipes</h2>
          <p>Stock + ISO + lab/dev notes + scan workflow—document the full analog pipeline.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Why recipes matter</h2>
        <p>
          Most photography knowledge lives in scattered YouTube comments, Discord chats, or “DM me” posts.
          Descubri makes recipes searchable, repeatable, and tied to real examples.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Learn faster:</strong> see settings + results side-by-side.</li>
          <li><strong>Share your process:</strong> give others something useful, not vague “vibes.”</li>
          <li><strong>Protect your work:</strong> share public basics, keep advanced details gated if you want.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section" id="faq">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <details>
            <summary>What is a “shot recipe”?</summary>
            <p>A shot recipe is the repeatable “how” behind an image: camera settings, film sim/preset/LUT/stock, and any key notes (time of day, lighting, etc.).</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can I share recipes without giving away my secret spot?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Descubri is built around spot protection—share fuzzed locations publicly and reveal exact coordinates only when you choose.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Is Descubri a marketplace too?</summary>
            <p>That’s the plan. Creators will be able to sell full-resolution files, RAWs, or licenses—directly from posts.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

